# Analysis of the Main Target Image

The main target image shows two distinct structures:

## Structure 1 (Left Structure):
- A central arrangement with a blue cross-shaped base (made of blue cubes)
- Four orange triangular prism blocks placed around the blue cross
- One orange cylindrical block standing vertically on top of the blue cross
- One orange triangular prism placed on top of the cylindrical block
- Total blocks: 1 blue cross (3 blue cubes) + 4 orange triangular prisms + 1 orange cylinder + 1 orange triangular prism = 9 blocks
- Layers: 3 layers (blue cross base, vertical cylinder, triangular prism top)

## Structure 2 (Right Structure):
- Two orange cylindrical blocks standing vertically as supports
- One yellow rectangular block placed horizontally across the top of the cylinders
- One orange triangular prism placed on top of the yellow block
- Total blocks: 2 orange cylinders + 1 yellow rectangular block + 1 orange triangular prism = 4 blocks
- Layers: 3 layers (cylindrical supports, yellow block, triangular prism top)

# Required Blocks from the Dictionary

For Structure 1:
- Block #1 (blue cube) x 3 (forming the blue cross base)
- Block #7 (orange cylinder) x 1 (vertical support)
- Block #11 or #12 (orange triangular prism) x 5 (4 around the blue cross, 1 on top)

For Structure 2:
- Block #7 (orange cylinder) x 2 (vertical supports)
- Block #3 or #4 (yellow rectangular block) x 1 (top horizontal piece)
- Block #11 or #12 (orange triangular prism) x 1 (on top of yellow block)

Looking more carefully at the orientations:
- For Structure 1, the triangular prisms around the blue cross appear to be Block #11
- For Structure 1, the top triangular prism appears to be Block #11
- For Structure 2, the yellow rectangular block appears to be Block #3
- For Structure 2, the top triangular prism appears to be Block #11

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 1
    Step3: Move block with index 1
    Step4: Move block with index 11
    Step5: Move block with index 11
    Step6: Move block with index 11
    Step7: Move block with index 11
    Step8: Move block with index 7
    Step9: Move block with index 11
    Step10: Move block with index 7
    Step11: Move block with index 7
    Step12: Move block with index 3
    Step13: Move block with index 11
}
```
